  <p>Finally, SEERAD has not conducted any empirical study of the impact of the Single Farm Payment Scheme in total on land values. Anecdotal evidence in 2005 from agricultural markets (the traditional marketplace for seasonal grazings) suggested that there were no significant changes in rental values in that year.</p>

